<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <p><MadCap:variable name="Outputs.WebHelp" /> is a Web-based Help format that is the precursor to HTML5, which is the recommended output type. It can run on almost any browser or platform. You can use <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.WebHelp" /> to create online documentation for the internet or an intranet, as well as for desktop applications.</p>
        <p>The <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.WebHelp" /> output consists of a collection of files that you will distribute to users. The output will be displayed in the user's internet browser window. The main entry file has an .htm extension.</p>
        <p><span class="Emphasis">WebHelp is deprecated in Flare, which means that it is slated to be removed in a future version, along with WebHelp Plus.</span>
        </p>
    </body>
</html>